    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-05T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-05T19:00:00-05:00" n="457"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d457">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.51/215a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-05T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 5, 1941—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>455. With the closing of the Paris office of the Embassy Vichy becomes the
                    permanent seat of the American Embassy to France. Beginning July 1 Department
                    contemplates placing Vichy on permanent status and making allotments for
                    operating expenses from the regular appropriations.…</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
